<p>I like a 1:3 water to milk ratio but you can always adjust as per your likings. Ginger and cardamom are usually the most used spices in tea, but cinnamom, cloves and a dash of black pepper powder works well too. If you want to try but are hesitant, you can always use them in small amounts. Experiment and find out what you like. 😋</p>

